The paper deals with data detection in wireless systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of FPGA designs and VLSI architecture suggests a focus on computer architecture (cs.AR). The algorithm-level optimizations and parallel processing techniques are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the development of reference designs and comparison to existing designs suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
